    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="529"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by General <persName type="from">Hsu
                            Tung-chang</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-10">10 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear General Marshall</hi>: Your Memorandum OSE 101, dated
                    30 May 1946,<note n="45" xml:id="d529fn45">Not printed.</note> with two
                    inclosures was received. However, regarding the final authority of American
                    representatives in items 1, 2 and 3 in the second inclosure (Agreement to Insure
                    the More Expeditious Functioning of Executive Headquarters,<note n="46"
                        xml:id="d529fn46">May 30, <ref target="#pg_914">p. 914</ref>.</note>) you
                    have not empowered yourself with that authority. The Generalissimo still wishes
                    you to refer to the 4th item in the first inclosure (Generalissimo’s letter to
                    you dated 28 May<note n="47" xml:id="d529fn47">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_907">p. 907</ref>.</note>)
                    regarding the final authority and that you should be empowered with such
                    authority. It is contemplated that this point be added into your proposal
                    “Agreement to Insure More Expeditious Functioning of Executive
                    Headquarters.”</p>
                <p>This letter is to notify you of the above and hope you will favor it with
                    consent. Also, a copy of this letter has been sent to General Chou En-lai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hsu Yung Chang</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >seal</hi>)</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
